Tutorial 2 - Using Wheel Encoder for Square Path Movement (sensor-based control)

  • Program that controls a Pioneer robot to follow a 2m by 2m square path.

  •  Pioneer 3-DX:

    • The diameter of the wheels is 195mm.
    • The distance between the two wheels is 330mm.

  • Go to "file" => "Open Sample World" => type "square_path" and find it

  • The sample code use time based control. It has a limitation, and inconsistent performance when the battery of robot drops.

  • Enhance the code by using the wheel encoder.

  • The sample code of moving the robot:

from controller import Robot

TIME_STEP = 64

MAX_VEL = 5.24

# create the Robot instance.
robot = Robot()

# get the motor devices
left_motor = robot.getDevice('left wheel')
right_motor = robot.getDevice('right wheel')
left_motor.setPosition(float("inf"))
right_motor.setPosition(float("inf"))

while robot.step(TIME_STEP) != -1:

   left_motor.setVelocity(MAX_VEL)
   right_motor.setVelocity(MAX_VEL)
  • The sample code of getting encoder values:
from controller import Robot
import time

TIME_STEP = 64
SPEED = 3.0

robot = Robot()

left_motor = robot.getDevice("left wheel")
right_motor = robot.getDevice("right wheel")
left_motor.setPosition(float("inf"))
right_motor.setPosition(float("inf"))

left_sensor = robot.getDevice("left wheel sensor")
right_sensor = robot.getDevice("right wheel sensor")
left_sensor.enable(TIME_STEP)
right_sensor.enable(TIME_STEP)


# Stop
left_motor.setVelocity(0)
right_motor.setVelocity(0)

# wait for the robot the boot up
for _ in range(10):
    robot.step(TIME_STEP)

# Get the encoder sensor values
initial_left = left_sensor.getValue()
initial_right = right_sensor.getValue()

for side in range(4):
    initial_left = left_sensor.getValue()
    initial_right = right_sensor.getValue()
    print(f"initial_left: {initial_left:.2f}")

    for _ in range(10):
        robot.step(TIME_STEP)

Reference : Michel, O. (2004). Webots: Professional mobile robot simulation. International Journal of Advanced Robotic Systems, 1(1), 39–42. https://doi.org/10.5772/5692
